oids.description:
For 10/100 Base-Tx Ethernet interfaces, this attribute is used to
             set the configuration options:
             auto(1): Auto-sensing;
             half10(2): 10BaseT (half duplex);
             full10(3): 10BaseT (full duplex);
             half100(4): 100BaseT (half duplex);
             full100(5): 100BaseT (full duplex);
             full1000(6): Gigabit Ethernet (full duplex);
             full10000(7): 10G Ethernet (full duplex);
